For some area musicians, the Detroit Music Awards is the social event of the season.
A video performance from Audio Birds (Sean Blackman, left, James Simonson and Larry Fratangelo) will be part of the online Detroit Music Awards, streaming Sunday evening.
Because the presenters don't have to commit to traveling downtown to the Fillmore theater, the Detroit Music Awards were able to snag some national talent to present awards this year.
He predicts that the awards ceremony and show, which is usually 90 minutes when done live, will clock in at just over an hour for the streamcast.
The Detroit Music Awards were founded in the late 1980s and the first award show was in 1992.